        "brief_summary": {
            "textblock": "This is a phase IV, open-label, prospective cohort study for 7 days.The recommended starting\n      dose of tolvaptan is 15 mg daily orally. The dose may be titrated on the next day at 15 mg\n      intervals up to 60 mg daily according to the serum sodium level response.Serum sodium level,\n      change in sodium level from baseline, quality of life (EQ-5D-3L), change in body weight,\n      edema, renal function, mortality and liver-related complications on day 7 and day 30 to\n      evaluate the efficacy of tolvaptan in cirrhotic patients with hyponatremia."
        }, 
        "brief_title": "Efficacy and Safety of Tolvaptan in Cirrhotic Patients With Hyponatremia", 
        "completion_date": {
            "#text": "June 2014", 
            "@type": "Anticipated"
        }, 
